est_bound <- st_read("eestimaa_wgs84.shp") 
## Reading layer `eestimaa_wgs84' from data source `C:\Users\admin\Documents\SCHOOL\R\eestimaa_wgs84.shp' using driver `ESRI Shapefile'

est_bound_3301 <- st_transform(est_bound, 3301)

est_bound_smpl <- st_simplify(est_bound_3301, preserveTopology = F, dTolerance = 200)

#Nearest neighbour

WinSpeed_sf <- st_as_sf(WinSpeed, coords= c("longitude", "latitude"), crs = 4326)

# Convert from lat-lon (WGS84) to Estonian official CRS (LEST-97 [epsg:3301])
WinSpeed_sf_3301 <- st_transform(WinSpeed_sf, 3301)



WinSpeed_sf_3301_gm <- st_union(WinSpeed_sf_3301)

# Create the Voronoi diagram: 
WinSpeed_sf_voronoi <- st_voronoi(WinSpeed_sf_3301_gm)
WinSpeed_sf_voronoi <- st_sf(WinSpeed_sf_voronoi)

## $ WinSpeed_sf_voronoi <GEOMETRYCOLLECTION [m]> GEOMETRYCOLLECTION (POL...

# Get the extent of interpolation area:

# create grid:

#Convert data frame to spatial points dataframa (SPDF):
WinSpeed_xy <- WinSpeed %>% dplyr::select(longitude, latitude, windspeed)
coordinates(WinSpeed_xy) <- ~ longitude + latitude



# convert from sf to spatial polygon data frame:
est_bound_sp <- as_Spatial(est_bound)

# create ppp object & set study area:
WinSpeed_xy_ppp <- as(WinSpeed_xy, "ppp")
vahe_estbound <- as(est_bound_sp, "owin")
WinSpeed_xy_ppp <- WinSpeed_xy_ppp[vahe_estbound]

#Polynomial

# define the grid:
grd <- as.data.frame(spsample(est_bound_sp, "regular", n = 10000))
names(grd)       <- c("X", "Y")
coordinates(grd) <- c("X", "Y")
gridded(grd)   <- TRUE  
fullgrid(grd)   <- TRUE 



# definition of CRS lest97:
lest97 <- CRS("+proj=lcc +lat_1=59.33333333333334 +lat_2=58 +lat_0=57.51755393055556 +lon_0=24 +x_0=500000 +y_0=6375000 +ellps=GRS80 +units=m +no_defs")

# definition of WGS84:
wgs84 <- CRS("+proj=longlat +ellps=WGS84")

# set CRS:
proj4string(WinSpeed_xy) <- wgs84
proj4string(grd) <- wgs84

# extent of spatial interpolation:
WinSpeed_xy@bbox <- as_Spatial(est_bound)@bbox

# 2nd polynomial model:
f.2 <- as.formula(windspeed ~ X + Y + I(X*X)+I(Y*Y) + I(X*Y))

# Add X and Y to airTemp_Df_xy:
WinSpeed_xy$X <- coordinates(WinSpeed_xy)[,1]
WinSpeed_xy$Y <- coordinates(WinSpeed_xy)[,2]

# Run the regression model
lm.2 <- lm(f.2, data = WinSpeed_xy)

# Use the regression model output to interpolate the surface
dat.2nd <- SpatialGridDataFrame(grd, data.frame(var1.pred = predict(lm.2, newdata=grd))) 

# Clip the interpolated raster
r   <- raster::raster(dat.2nd)
r.m <- raster::mask(r, as_Spatial(est_bound))

r.m_df <- raster::as.data.frame(r.m, xy=T)
class(r.m_df)
## [1] "data.frame"
r.m_df <- r.m_df %>% filter(!is.na(var1.pred))
glimpse(r.m_df)
## Observations: 10,047
## Variables: 3
## $ x         <dbl> 25.69991, 25.72585, 24.99957, 25.02551, 25.69991, 25...

## $ var1.pred <dbl> 5.306880, 5.302913, 5.239629, 5.239836, 5.185407, 5....
# data classes (quantiles):
r.m_df <- r.m_df %>% mutate(quant = ntile(var1.pred, 5))

# kriging

#define model
P_gs <- gstat::gstat(formula = windspeed~1, locations = WinSpeed_xy)

P_v <- variogram(P_gs, width = 1)

#create semi-variogram
P_semivariog <- variogram(windspeed ~ 1, locations = WinSpeed_xy, data = WinSpeed_xy)
plot(P_semivariog)

psill <- P_semivariog$gamma[nrow(P_semivariog)]
nugget <- P_semivariog$gamma[1]
range <- ceiling(P_semivariog$dist[nrow(P_semivariog)])

P_model.variog <- vgm(psill = psill, model = "Sph", nugget = nugget, range = range)

# fit model:
P_fit.variog <- fit.variogram(P_semivariog, P_model.variog)
## Warning in fit.variogram(P_semivariog, P_model.variog): No convergence
## after 200 iterations: try different initial values?
plot(P_semivariog, P_fit.variog) # if the model doesn't fit well, try to find better!

P_krig <- krige(formula = windspeed ~ 1, locations = WinSpeed_xy, newdata = grd, model = P_model.variog)
## [using ordinary kriging]
plot(P_krig)

P_r <- raster::raster(P_krig)
P_r.m <- raster::mask(P_r, est_bound)

P_r.m_df <- raster::as.data.frame(P_r.m, xy=T)
P_r.m_df <- P_r.m_df %>% dplyr::filter(!is.na(var1.pred))

P_r.m_df <- P_r.m_df %>% rename(speed = `var1.pred`)

glimpse(P_r.m_df)
